parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the BOSCH CP4 high-pressure fuel pump can cause metal shavings to be released throughout the fuel system, leading to catastrophic engine failure, stalling, and potential accidents.
Engine coolant leaks can cause engine overheating, damage to engine components, and potentially lead to engine failure, stalling, and accidents.
A faulty engine can cause stalling, loss of power, and potential accidents, especially if the failure occurs while driving at high speeds.
The failure of the SCR active reservoir can cause the check engine warning light to illuminate, and if left unrepaired, can lead to engine damage and stalling.
The failure of the EGR cooler can cause stalling, loss of power, and potential accidents, especially if the failure occurs while driving at high speeds.
The failure of the timing chain can cause engine stalling, loss of power, and potential accidents, especially if the failure occurs while driving at high speeds.
The failure of the turbo can cause loss of power, stalling, and potential accidents, especially if the failure occurs while driving at high speeds.
The failure of the DPF can cause engine stalling, loss of power, and potential accidents, especially if the failure occurs while driving at high speeds.
The failure of the high-pressure fuel pump can cause engine stalling, loss of power, and potential accidents, especially if the failure occurs while driving at high speeds.
The failure of the high-pressure fuel pump can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: the power train failure message is displayed
the vehicle is unable to restart
the entire fuel system needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Delayed Recall Repair for Fuel System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delayed availability of parts for the recall repair can leave vehicles with faulty fuel systems on the road, increasing the risk of accidents or stalling.
symptoms: The vehicle has been notified of a recall
but the parts are not yet available
the manufacturer has exceeded a reasonable amount of time for the recall repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the HPFP can cause the vehicle to suddenly stall or lose power, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or injuries, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: Sudden engine stall or loss of power
metal debris found in the fuel tank

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the driveshaft can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, and potentially resulting in fatalities.
symptoms: oil leaking from the oil pan

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause sudden loss of power, stalling, and inability to shift gears, leading to accidents and potentially resulting in fatalities.
symptoms: error messages on the control center.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic transmission interlock can cause the vehicle to become stuck in park or neutral, making it difficult or impossible to move the vehicle, leading to accidents and potentially resulting in fatalities.
symptoms: Vehicle stuck in park or neutral
error messages on the control center
no manual override or documented procedure to override the interlock.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the EGR valve can cause power loss, leading to accidents and potentially resulting in fatalities.
